<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-74-1089 </DOCNO><TEXT>As a part of work to make a Japanese criticality safety handbook, we carriedout large amount of criticality calculations to obtain critical sizes(mass,sphere volume, cylinder diameter and slab thickness) and subcriticalsize limits. The calculations were performed with a criticality safetycode system JACS developed in JAERI. This paper describes a method ofthe calculation, results and some comparisons our results with foreigncriticality handbooks.</TEXT></DOC>